32 new cases of political violence have been recorded in KwaZulu-Natal since June last year. In 2018 President Cyril Ramaphosa formed an Inter-Ministerial Committee to look into such cases. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah is following this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - More than 30 new cases of political violence have been recorded in KwaZulu-Natal since June last year. Police Minister Bheki Cele gave an update on the situation on Wednesday. READ: Mkhize calls for end to political killings There has been an increase in politically-related murders in the lead up to – and since - last year’s elections. In 2018, President Cyril Ramaphosa formed an Inter-Ministerial Committee to look into such cases.